However, I can share the general coverage outlined in Sound Physicians' policy:

Annual Deductibles: $1,500 for an individual or $3,000 for a family, resetting each January 1st.

Copays: Primary care visits are $25, specialist visits are $60, urgent care is $75, emergency room visits are $250, telemedicine visits are $20, and telemedicine mental health visits are $15.

Outpatient Surgery: Covered at 80% after your deductible is met, with you responsible for the remaining 20% up to your out-of-pocket maximum.

Out-of-Pocket Maximum: $5,000 for an individual or $10,000 for a family. Once you reach this limit, the plan covers 100% of covered services for the rest of the year.

Prescription Drugs: Generic medications have a $10 copay, brand-name medications are $40, and specialty drugs are $100.

Mental Health Services: Covered at the same rate as primary care, with a $25 copay for in-person sessions and $15 for telehealth sessions.

For information specific to your personal coverage, I recommend calling 855-768-6363 or contacting your insurance provider directly.

